title: Country diary: Sometimes only the most rotten fruit will do | Mark Cocker
summary: In Buxton, Derbyshire, most of the discovered apples have been consumed by jackdaws and crows. However, a group of a dozen red admirals has arrived, indicating their interest in the apples. The presence of these butterflies highlights the diverse interactions within the local ecosystem.

summary: A Kiwi steeplechaser reflects on a near-fatal fall during the heats, viewing it as a possible blessing in disguise. This incident may have motivated him to perform exceptionally well. Ultimately, he went on to achieve historic success in Tokyo.

title: ‘Cricket gave me everything’: South African sports star brings township children into the game
summary: Gary Kirsten, a renowned international cricketer and coach, considers his involvement in Khayelitsha, Cape Town, as one of the pinnacle experiences of his cricketing journey. His work there highlights his commitment to community development through sports. Kirsten's efforts in the area emphasize the positive impact of cricket beyond just the game.
